question: Jonsa #6!
answer:
6. (angst) “fuck you.”

“Fuck you.”

The words yearn to be unleashed, so Jon bites the inside of his cheek. His fury longs to be put into action, so he clenches his fist and hides them behind his back.

He can’t exactly strike nor insult their new king.

Aegon Targaryen, he’s said he is, Rhaegar Targaryen’s son. Young Griff, Jon’s heard others call him, and he sticks to that name, if only in his head, disbelieving, unwilling to humor the boy who’d stormed Westeros with a huge army after they’d all fought for their lives. Who’d taken the Iron Throne by force, much like his ancestor over three hundred years past, if only without fucking dragons.

The boy who’d come to take Sansa away.

His Sansa.

“What say you, Lord Snow?” The name rankles. “Lady Stark will look quite fetching draped in red and black, don’t you think?”

“She’ll look beautiful,” he blurts out, unthinking, and curses when Young Griff turns to give him a curious look, so he adds, “Your Grace.”

“Beautiful, indeed,” he agrees, and turns to look out over the parapets. “She’ll make a good queen, compassionate and kind.” It’s the smirk that comes then what has Jon gripping his forearms to not fucking lunge. “She’ll make a good wife.”

Jaw clenching, Jon averts his gaze as the memory of days prior assault him. Of Sansa and Aegon walking through the glass gardens, her hand tucked under his elbow; of her smiles and giggles and the lovely blush tinting her cheeks red. Of the gentle way the king tucked a lock of red hair behind her ear and-

She kissed him. The image of Sansa leaning into the blue-haired boy and kissing him will be forever burned into his mind, the pain searing his soul. I’ve no right, no right to feel anything- my sister, Sansa is just my sister. I can’t, can’t feel anything-

He’d not meant to witness that.

Jon had not meant to welcome her into his arms later that night, either, softly soothing her worries and making promises he cannot possibly keep.

Should not keep.

“I don’t want to go back to that place-” But how can he ignore such a plea? Gods, but he can’t. “I want to stay here in Winterfell… say, say you’ll help me.”

His hand reaches for his sword, grips the hilt tightly, his feet shift- then he stops. Freezes, the part of him he’d thought he’d lost after his resurrection makes him stop. The soft whisper in the back of his mind, tantalising, treason, treason, that’s treason.

But then another, louder, stronger, Sansa’s, lips pressed against his cheek, a murmur of his name:

“Jon…”

“Well,” the king turns to face him, smirking, “I’d like to see my betrothed, Lord Snow, if you would escort me.”

Jon blinks and feels his lips pull up in a sharp smile. “I will.”

“I don’t want to go back to that place-” But how can he ignore such a plea? Gods, but he can’t. “I want to stay here in Winterfell… say, say you’ll help me.”

His hand reaches for his sword, grips the hilt tightly, his feet shift- then he stops. Freezes, the part of him he’d thought he’d lost after his resurrection makes him stop. The soft whisper in the back of his mind, tantalising, treason, treason, that’s treason.

But then another, louder, stronger, Sansa’s, lips pressed against his cheek, a murmur of his name:

“Jon…”

“Well,” the king turns to face him, smirking, “I’d like to see my betrothed, Lord Snow, if you would escort me.”

Jon blinks and feels his lips pull up in a sharp smile. “I will.”

“Fuck you.”

The words yearn to be unleashed, so Jon bites the inside of his cheek. His fury longs to be put into action, so he clenches his fist and hides them behind his back.

He can’t exactly strike nor insult their new king.

Aegon Targaryen, he’s said he is, Rhaegar Targaryen’s son. Young Griff, Jon’s heard others call him, and he sticks to that name, if only in his head, disbelieving, unwilling to humor the boy who’d stormed Westeros with a huge army after they’d all fought for their lives. Who’d taken the Iron Throne by force, much like his ancestor over three hundred years past, if only without fucking dragons.

The boy who’d come to take Sansa away.

His Sansa.

“What say you, Lord Snow?” The name rankles. “Lady Stark will look quite fetching draped in red and black, don’t you think?”

“She’ll look beautiful,” he blurts out, unthinking, and curses when Young Griff turns to give him a curious look, so he adds, “Your Grace.”

“Beautiful, indeed,” he agrees, and turns to look out over the parapets. “She’ll make a good queen, compassionate and kind.” It’s the smirk that comes then what has Jon gripping his forearms to not fucking lunge. “She’ll make a good wife.”

Jaw clenching, Jon averts his gaze as the memory of days prior assault him. Of Sansa and Aegon walking through the glass gardens, her hand tucked under his elbow; of her smiles and giggles and the lovely blush tinting her cheeks red. Of the gentle way the king tucked a lock of red hair behind her ear and-

She kissed him. The image of Sansa leaning into the blue-haired boy and kissing him will be forever burned into his mind, the pain searing his soul. I’ve no right, no right to feel anything- my sister, Sansa is just my sister. I can’t, can’t feel anything-

He’d not meant to witness that.

Jon blinks and feels his lips pull up in a sharp smile. “I will.”

summary: I received the Targaryen history book for Christmas, and reading it is putting me back into the ASOIAF mood a bit. Interested in...
body:
I received the Targaryen history book for Christmas, and reading it is putting me back into the ASOIAF mood a bit. Interested in fics. However, my requirements have proven too stringent it seems?

Shoot me a rec if you have any good fics which are:

  • Jon Snow-centric
  • plot/adventure heavy
  • not Jonsa, Jonerys, or Jon/anyone who is related to or grew up thinking he was related to
  • that’s it
  • Ghost heavy would be nice too but really the main sticking point seems to be the ‘no incest/only avoids it by technicality’ thing
